          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1680691659981-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>potato wedges</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for an initial 10 min, then add the <strong>green beans</strong> to the pot and cook for a further 5 min or until everything is tender</p><p>Once done, drain everything and add your<strong> cider vinegar</strong>, a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
